<P><H1 align=center>CUSTOMER CONTACT HISTORY – CR025</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>On this screen notes can be added to show any customer contact made </P>
<P><H3>Add: </H3>to add a note, click on ‘Add’, and the 
‘Contact History Detail’ dialogue box appears Contact History Detail (dialogue 
box)
<P></P>
<P><H3>Contact Reason: </H3>select the relevant reason from 
the dropdown list.
<P></P>
<P>Other Reason: if ‘other’ is selected from the above list, the reason must be 
completed in this field</P>
<P><H3>Details: </H3>this is a free-form box to type in any 
notes from the customer contact
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>click on ‘OK’ to save the details and return 
to the main screen
<P></P>
<P><H3>Edit: </H3>to view a note, highlight the contact and 
click on ‘Edit’. This displays the note.
<P></P>
<P>To delete a record, click the ‘Delete this record’ radio button in the bottom 
left of the screen.</P>
<P>Click on ‘OK’ to return to the main screen. In the main box, there will be a 
‘Yes’ next to the record under ‘Deleted?’. The note can still be viewed by 
clicking on ‘Edit’.</P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>click on OK once this screen has been 
completed.
<P></P>

